Job Description:
Overall Purpose of the Role: 
• Providing administrative support and office management include managing office stock, preparing regular reports (e.g. expenses and office budgets);
• Assist MJQF team for cash request/settlement, purchasing materials, quotation and other relevant tasks;
• Assist Program Manager to coordinate staff performance and management.

** Scope of Work 
• Provide administrative support to MJQF staff and their field activities in target area;
• Assist Program Manager for staff performance and management and problem solving;
• Assist MJQF team to coordinate and response to emergency cases.

** Typical tasks for Admin:
• Manage office supplies stock and place orders;
• Prepare/update MJQF asset list and disposal;
• Organize a filing system for important and confidential MJQF documents;
• Answer queries by employees and clients;
• Update office policies as needed;
• Make appointments with other for MJQF meeting;
• Book meeting rooms and vehicle for project as required;
• Distribute and store correspondence (e.g. letters, emails and packages);
• Prepare reports and presentations with statistical data, as assigned;
• Arrange travel and accommodations;
• Schedule in-house and external events;
• Suggest changes or improvements to increase accuracy, efficiency, and cost reductions;
• Perform in cross-functional team approach and job responsibilities;
• Assist MJQF team coordinating/responding to emergency case happened within program target area (support sick people to hospital);
• Set prioritize work and produce quality results with timeframe set.

** Typical tasks for HR: 
• Assist manager to conduct new employee orientations;
• Advise to staff on policies like equal employment opportunity and sexual harassment;
• Direct disciplinary procedures;
• Produce payroll for program staff;
• Prepare monthly staff movement;
• Print individual staff sick leave and annual leave and check to ensure have enough support documents and submit for approval;
• Revise/print MJQF organization chart for approval and submit in quarterly basis;
• Good understanding of the organization's overall business and its objectives;
• Able to provide orientation to new staff and partners about MJQF.

Planning (business plans and forecast):
• Budget templates preparations;
• Work with commercial functions and support them to insure timely, relevant and reasonable budgets (sales, prices, discounts, commercial expenses) with sufficient details. Consolidation of planed reports and key-in to local ERP system;
• Business plan and forecast profitability reports preparation (SKU/Brands/Category/Regions etc.)
Month closing:
• Tracking and checking the submitted expenses/compensations whether they approved and budgeted;
• Accruals preparation with commercial functions (discounts and commercial expenses);
Reporting and analysis:
• Commercial reports preparation and analysis: Sales, Discounts, Commercial Expenses, profitability reports preparation in certain dimensions and formats (by SKU/Brands/Category/Regions etc.) 
• Periodic and timely commercial reports tracking – analysis of deviation (vs last year, budget, last forecast), addressing the issues and proposing solutions;
• Profitability analysis by SKU/Brands/Category/Regions etc.
Finance rationale and Profitability analysis:
• Commercial promotions/activities/proposals analysis;
• Commercial ad-hoc cases analysis;
Tools/System projects:
• Automation projects - participating in projects related to improve ERP system and reporting.
Commercial Function Supporting:
• Participation in cross-functional projects;
• Develop Partnership;

Job Requirement:
• University graduate or above in Finance or Maths;
• CPA, ACCA or other accounting qualification holders preferred
• 3+ Experience in FMCG in commercial controlling function preferred;
• Knowledge of finance, accounting, budgeting, and cost control principles;
• Analytical skills;
• Familiar with ERP system (NAV, SAP or Oracle preferable;
• Experience in BI tools is preferred;
• Good working knowledge of Excel & Powerpoint;
• Commercial understanding;
• Organized, responsive, able to work under pressure and to focus on delivering results;
• Communication skills.
• Good command of English

